  "description": "The piece of text talks about how to deploy Jenkins in Kubernetes by creating a Jenkins role, authorizing it and deploying the Jenkins application. Jenkins is open source CI/CD software used to automate building, testing, and deploying software. Jenkins installation supports running in system packages, Docker or through a standalone Java program. Docker deployment provided convenience, and Kubernetes orchestration is used. To provide data persistence, PVC (Persistent Volume Claim) is created. For Jenkins authorization, Jenkins role and role binding are created. Finally, Jenkins application is deployed with a specification of one replica, termination grace period in seconds, Jenkins service account, Jenkins container and image.",
